One of the problems with AO3 is that the tags are essentially useless, because there's nobody driving the bus. There is no standardization. No one is requiring the people who post content to use or not use any particular tag. Some authors there genuinely don't seem to grasp that there is a tag system, or how to use it, or what it's for. Mind you, AO3 isn't the only place to have that kind of problem, but it's really noticeable there. It'd help if the admins at AO3 made up a list of tags and forced people posting to select pre-created standardized tags from drop-down boxes, like the Pit of Voles has, instead of just making stuff up as they go. But that's a bottomless timesink. And there are people who'd try to hack any such system just on general principles, just out of spite.
